commitResults.messageTitle: Implement skeletal version of Duke
Add the ability to store whatever text entered by the user and display them back to the user when requested
Add the ability to mark tasks as done Add Task class to represent tasks
Add support for tracking three types of tasks: Todo, Deadline, Event
Add semi-automated text UI testing
Add error handling for two types of errors Add DukeException class, handle unknown command and todo without description
Add support for deleting tasks from the list
Fix excessive line length of code
Add load data functionality
Add ability to save the tasks in the hard disk automatically whenever the task list changes
Change delete tasks to save tasks automatically
Change deadline and event dates from String to java.time.LocalDate
Replace all deadline and event dates String with java.time.LocalDate
Write implementation for Ui, Parser, Storage, TaskList, Command and *Command classes. Change LocalDate to LocalDateTime.
Integrate previously written classes into Duke
Put all classes in duke package
Add JUnit test for Duke and Parser
Add header comments to *Command classes
Fix code to comply with the given coding standard
Add find feature Give users a way to find a task by searching for a keyword
Correct mainClassName in shadowJar
Use CheckStyle and fix coding style violations
Add skeletal JavaFX implementation
Add implementation for getResponse in Duke class
Fix checkstyle violations
Package *Command classes and *Task classes and remove Ui class
Correct mainClassName for shadowJar
Fix styling issues and add ignore case functionality for commands
Add assertions
commitResults.messageBody:
There are several assumptions in the Storage and Duke classes.
It is assumed that the storage location and the storage field of Duke
has been initialized successfully.

To ensure the assumptions hold, let's add some assertions.

commitResults.messageTitle: Improve code quality of Parser class
commitResults.messageBody:
The parse method of Parser was very long, affecting its readability.
Separating it into smaller methods and practicing the
Single Level of Abstraction Principle here will improve the readability.

Let's create new methods to be used in the parse method to make it
more readable and improve the code quality.

commitResults.messageTitle: Use Streams in TaskList class
commitResults.messageBody:
Streams can be used in the findTask method to filter out tasks matching
the given keyword and collect them in a list.

This will make the code shorter and more readable.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add help command
commitResults.messageBody:
Typing 'help' allows user to see a list of commands and the correct
input format.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add alias for adding task
commitResults.messageBody:
't' is an alias for todo, 'd' is an alias for deadline and 'e' is an
alias for event. Having aliases will make the command syntax friendlier.
